    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">Pieter Nanninck to Miklós Oláh (Leuven, 30 June 1537)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He wants to get <hi rend="italic">Athila</hi> back
                            from Conrad Wackers, who cannot get enough of it and was gushing how he
                            also read it quickly and reveled in it. He will not allow for this book
                            to go unpublished. They should put a poem at the beginning. 2. He is
                            asking for his opinion as an editor, here it is: who could write more
                            authentically about these events, topography, and the diversity of
                            peoples, if not a Hungarian eyewitness? He compares Oláh’s style of
                            history writing to that of Strabo and Herodotus. Nanninck salutes the
                            fact that Oláh used the names of places in his own language –
                            Ciceronians like to use words and name forms that never existed, but
                            Oláh is right not to follow them. 3. He especially liked how he writes
                            about the kings’ fate, and his speeches are fantastic. Although the
                            Turks have taken most of Hungary, Oláh is now returning all of it
                            through his book. Oláh asked him to emend his poem, but there was
                            nothing to be corrected in it. 4. Nanninck asks Oláh to accept the
                            bearer of the letter, the excellent Rutger Pathius, who is well-versed
                            in Latin and Greek, into his circle, but if cannot, he should at least
                            pay for his travel expenses for the way back. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/C16F1A8C-487B-4F3F-A754-412FF6119001
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Petrus Nannius Nicolao Olao salutem. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Nihil ad te scripsi, <del corresp="Olahus">Erudissime</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Eruditissime</add> Patrone, quia nec sciebam,
                    ubi ageres, nec habebam, per <choice>
                        <orig>quas</orig>
                        <supplied>quos</supplied>
                    </choice> mitterem. De <hi rend="italic">Athila</hi> tuo vere erudito opere
                    habeo, quod doleam, habeo etiam, quod </p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/59A33594-0A4E-4D5B-82D7-86363978A2D1
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.3">conquerar ultra enim unam hebdamadam, et vix eam plenam mihi eius
                    usus permissus non est, hactenus enim eum detinuit
                        <persName>Goclenius</persName>.<note xml:id="note.1">Conrad Wackers.</note>
                    Credo nondum satur eius lectionis, nam mirificas de eo mihi decantavit laudes,
                    dedit autem eo tempore, quo nihil mihi unquam vel tumultuosius vel occupatius.
                    Sed quid ad te mea negotia, legi avidissime libros illos, <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >geluatus</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">helluatus</add> sum in eis,
                    usque ad summas aures miris voluptatibus me implevi. Usuram mihi non longiorem
                    concessam fuisse etiam nunc doleo, non omittam, non intermittam ullum laborem,
                    donec vel ex prelo, vel a te eum recuperavero. Cupio frontispicio carmen aliquod
                    praefligere, <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">etsi</add> nihil possum, quia
                    tamen eam operam Holao sum impensurus, puto me aliquid posse. Si natura negat,
                    amor est, <choice>
                        <orig>quae</orig>
                        <supplied>qui</supplied>
                    </choice> carmina condit. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">[2.] Cupis meam censuram, audi, breviter dico, quod
                        <persName>Conradus</persName> dixit: me non minus id opus amare, quam
                    admirari. <del corresp="Olahus">Quid</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                        >Quis</add> enim fidelior in rebus gestis trandendis, quis certior in
                    topographiis, quis distinctior omni genere varietatis, qui te Hungarum esse
                    nescit, satis tamen id colligit ἐκ τῆς τῶν πάντων ἀκριβείας<note xml:id="note.2"
                        >‘from an all-encompassing precision’.</note> vel Hungarum αὐτόπτην.<note
                        xml:id="note.3">‘witness’.</note> Absit adulatio a nostra amicitia, quam et
                    tu odisti et ego non fero, videris mihi plurimorum authorum virtutes
                    coniunxisse, habes in locis describendis exactissimam curam
                        <persName>Strabonis</persName>, ubi etiam tua illa mathematicarum
                    disciplinarum peritia non obscuriter lucet, nec ibi gratiae illae
                        <persName>Herodoti</persName> absunt. Multa parodoxa de moribus gentium
                    afferuntur non e mendaciis, ut ille fecit, sed ex fide rerum deprompta; adsunt
                    deinde locorum vocabula nativo sono expressa,<note xml:id="note.4">Oláh also
                        wrote geographical names in <hi rend="italic">Athila</hi> and <hi
                            rend="italic">Hungaria</hi> in Hungarian.</note> non κακοζηλίᾳ<note
                        xml:id="note.5">‘by artificially imitating (the Latin language)’.</note>
                    Latini sermonis in alienam speciem deformata, quod cum maxime cupit
                        <persName>Lucianus</persName> in historiis observari, nescio, an ullus
                    praeter te vere praestitit. </p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/9837538A-D32C-4E87-8666-B508525DB441
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Veteres barbarum vocum sonos assecuti non sunt neoterici, qui toti
                    sunt in mollioribus sonis, reformidant, quare omnia ita fingunt ac refingunt, ut
                    qui ibi nati sunt, nomen patriae suae non agnoscant. Vere stultum genus, quibus
                    ferme idem accidit, quod vulgo musicorum, qui omissis verbis et sententiis nihil
                    aucupantur, nisi gargalismo sonorum aures implere, pectus inane relinquere. His
                    Ciceronianis (hoc titulo enim sibi blandiuntur) si vis servire, quorum mundus
                    nunc plenus est aut asperitas illa vocum mollienda est, aut rarius istiusmodi
                    voces inspargendae; si doctis probari vis, id agendum est, quod agis, nec de
                    fide rerum vel apex mutandus. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.6">[3.] Mirifice id mihi placuit, quod ubi de fortunis regii tui
                    generis enarrationem texis, quasi alienum te geris nec tuorum vel laetis, vel
                    adversis, tui affectus produntur. Hoc <persName>Thucydidis</persName>, hoc
                        <persName>Xenophontis</persName>, hoc <persName>Salustii</persName>. In
                    orationibus vehemens es vel, ut <del corresp="Olahus">melius</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">mollius</add> aiunt Graeci δεινός,<note
                        xml:id="note.6">‘overwhelming’.</note> et quod ego maxime amo, sermonem
                    personis attemperas et ipsorum indoli et praesenti fortunae <choice>
                        <orig>congruam</orig>
                        <supplied>congruum</supplied>
                    </choice>. Abstulit Turca magna ex parte Hungariam, tu nobis totam reddidisti,
                    et ut <persName>Iosephus</persName><hi rend="italic"> Antiquitatibus</hi><note
                        xml:id="note.7">Josephus Flavius’ <hi rend="italic">Antiquitates
                            Judaicae.</hi></note> suis memoriae suorum consuluit, qui iam maximis
                    cladibus ceciderant, ita tu res gestas maiorum tuorum, cum iam periisse
                    quodammodo viderentur, aeternitati consecravisti, ac nescio, an eodem zelo, quo
                    ipse, inductus fueris, certe idem praestitisti. <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >Camen</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr">Carmen</add><note
                        xml:id="note.8">Probably the opening poem of <hi rend="italic"
                        >Hungaria</hi>, or Erasmus of Rotterdam’s epitaph.</note> tuum emendavi, ut
                    volebas, vel potius mutavi, ut iussisti, nulla enim emendatione opus fuit. Scis,
                    quantopere mihi tua carmina placent, hoc mihi tamen, quod
                        <persName>Craneveldio</persName><note xml:id="note.9">Frans van
                        Cranevelt.</note> dedisti, prae omnibus placet. τὰ δευτέρα ἀμείνω, εἰ καὶ τὰ
                    πάντα <choice>
                        <orig>κάλα</orig>
                        <supplied>καλά</supplied>
                    </choice>.<note xml:id="note.10">‘the second ones are better, although all of
                        them are pretty’.</note></p>
                <pb facs="https://www.eleveltar.hu/kereso-portlet/spring/digitalcontent/getcontent/preservica/63941F73-0FE2-4D4B-A857-7339EBF63B6D
                    "/>
                <p xml:id="p.7">[4.] Desino, ne, dum vera dico, tuae modestiae supra verum dicere
                    videar. Hic,<note xml:id="note.11">Rutger Pathius, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Polet</hi> 1936, 256.</note> qui litteras adfert, iuvenis est probis et
                    honestis parentibus natus et mediocris fortunae, mores illius per quadriennium,
                    quod mecum vixit, probissimos <del corresp="Olahus">expersus</del><add
                        corresp="Olahus" type="corr">expertus</add> sum; placidum illi ingenium et
                    fidum, nihil in moribus vanum aut futile, arcani tenax, promptus ad obsequia et
                    Graece et Latine non male peritus, hunc talem esse mea fide polliceor, quare si
                        <del corresp="Olahus">tum</del> dominus <del corresp="Olahus"
                        >Rugerus</del><add corresp="Olahus" type="corr"
                            ><persName>Rutgerus</persName></add><note xml:id="note.12">Rutger
                        Ressen.</note> eum in suum famulitium suscipiet, recte faciet, sin minus,
                    rogo, ut iuveni ad nos redituro viaticum refundatur. Optime vale, Optime
                    Patrone. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.8">Pridie Kalendas Iulias, raptim, ut vides. 1537.</p>
            </div>
